data.enText: a competition in which people try to win sth

data.chText: 参加 / 赢得竞赛；竞赛失败

data.enText: a struggle to gain control or power
a contest for the leadership of the party

data.chText: （表示竞争中的一方过于强大或出色）完全不是对手，毫无竞争可言
data.enText: used to say that one side in a competition is so much stronger or better than the other that it is sure to win easily
to take part in a competition, election, etc. and try to win it

data.chText: 有三位候选人角逐领导权。

data.enText: a hotly/fiercely/keenly contested game (= one in which the players try very hard to win and the scores are close)
to formally oppose a decision or statement because you think it is wrong
to contest a will (= try to show that it was not correctly made in law)

data.chText: 这桩离婚案没有人提出异议。

simple_means.memory_skill: con 共同 + test 测试；证据 → 共同论证 → 争论

ex.enText: There is a tennis match tomorrow.
How many matches are there this season?

synonyms.bx: 通常指体育比赛，一般在两人或两队之间进行。

ex.chText: 他是那次摄影比赛的优胜者。
ex.enText: He was the winner of that photography competition.

synonyms.bx: 指体育比赛或知识、技巧等方面的比赛。

ex.chText: 拼写比赛下周将在我们学校举行。
ex.enText: The spelling contest will take place at our school next week.

ex.chText: 你将参加新秀选拔赛吗？
ex.enText: Are you going to attend the talent contest?

synonyms.bx: 尤指某种技能活动或体育运动的比赛。

ex.chText: 她更喜欢和家人一起看电视转播的比赛。
ex.enText: She prefers to see games on TV with her family.

ex.chText: 西班牙队对阵法国队的那场世界杯比赛结果如何？
ex.enText: What's the result of the Spain's World Cup game against France?

synonyms.bx: 泛指有一定规则的比赛，如游戏、体育运动等。

data.chText: （表示竞争中的一方过于强大或出色）完全不是对手，毫无竞争可言
data.enText: used to say that one side in a competition is so much stronger or better than the other that it is sure to win easily

tr: an occasion on which a winner is selected from among two or more contestants
to make the subject of dispute, contention, or litigation
example: They contested the outcome of the race

value.boxr_value: The noun is pronounced /'kɒntest/. The verb is pronounced /kən'test/. 名词读作  /'kɒntest/，动词读作 /kən'test/。

value.def: A contest is a competition or game in which people try to win.

example.ex: Few contests in the recent history of British boxing have been as thrilling.
example.tran: 英国近年的拳击比赛中很少有如此激动人心的。

value.def: A contest is a struggle to win power or control.

example.ex: The state election due in November will be the last such ballot before next year's presidential contest...
example.tran: 定于11月举行的州选举将是明年总统竞选前最后一次此类投票选举。

example.ex: ...a clear contest between church and state.
example.tran: 教会与政府之间明显的争斗

value.def: If someone contests an election or competition, they take part in it and try to win it.

example.ex: He quickly won his party's nomination to contest the elections.
example.tran: 他很快获得了本党提名,角逐大选。
各方争奇斗艳、难分高下的地区花卉展

value.tran: 争取赢得(选举、比赛等);角逐

value.def: If you contest a statement or decision, you object to it formally because you think it is wrong or unreasonable.

example.ex: Your former employer has to reply within 14 days in order to contest the case...
example.tran: 你的前任雇主若对本案存有异议，必须在14天内予以答复。

example.ex: Gender discrimination is a hotly contested issue.
example.tran: 性别歧视是一个争论激烈的话题。

无赛事；无竞争；不抗辩；无争议

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to test, witness 测试；证据
rootsaffixes.title: test(i)

partsOfSpeech.dec: at 加强 + test 测试；证据 → 一再测试 → 证明
con 共同 + test 测试；证据 → 共同论证 → 争论
contest 竞赛；争论 + ant 表人 → 竞争者
de 去掉，取消 + test 测试；证据 → 不愿〔出面〕作证 → 憎恶
pro 在前 + test 测试；证据 → 在前面论证 → 坚决声明 → 引申为表示抗议
testi 测试；证据 + fy 使… → 用证据证明 → 证实
testi 测试；证据 + mon 提醒 + ial …的 → 供提醒的证据 → 证明书
testi 测试；证据 + mony 表结果、状态 → 证据；证词
